<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-12-12T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-12-12T08:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">875.00/164: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tirana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-12-12T14:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">December 12,
                                        1924—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 7:55
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>91. Threats of incursion by refugees from Yugoslav territory increase as
                            the date for the election approaches. Reports in the foreign press that
                            a revolution has started in Albania are premature.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>